{
  "text": "In summary, our set of data would support the hypothesis that fasting whole-body and hepatic energy metabolism is not abnormal in individuals with fatty liver when compared to matched controls in agreement with findings generated using different methodological tools [CITATION_1] , in contrast with the finding within the skeletal muscle [CITATION_2] and the heart of insulin-resistant individuals [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
